                     <bitWidth>1</bitWidth>
                  </field>
                  <field>
                     <name>CHNG2</name>
                     <description>This bit is set to 1 whenever the value in Bit2 in this register changes. This bit is set to 0 whenever the 4 data bits in\n      this register are transmitted to the Host by a Slave-to-Master Virtual Wire transaction. It is also set to 0 when this entire register is\n      reset, ignoring any change in the data bit value caused by the reset event.</description>
